begin
reserve V for RealLinearSpace;
reserve u for (VECTOR of V);
reserve v for (VECTOR of V);
reserve w for (VECTOR of V);
reserve a for Real;
reserve b for Real;
theorem
Th23: (u,v // u,w implies (u,v // v,w or u,w // w,v))
proof
assume A1: u,v // u,w;
now
assume (u <> v & u <> w);
then consider a,b such that A2: ( a * ( v - u ) ) = ( b * ( w - u ) ) and A3: ( 0 ) < a and A4: ( 0 ) < b by A1,CKB8:1;
( w - v ) = ( ( w - u ) + ( u - v ) ) by CKB2:1
.= ( ( w - u ) - ( v - u ) ) by RLVECT_1:33;
then A5: ( a * ( w - v ) ) = ( ( a * ( w - u ) ) - ( b * ( w - u ) ) ) by A2,RLVECT_1:34
.= ( ( a - b ) * ( w - u ) ) by RLVECT_1:35
.= ( ( b - a ) * ( u - w ) ) by CKB5:1;
( v - w ) = ( ( v - u ) + ( u - w ) ) by CKB2:1
.= ( ( v - u ) - ( w - u ) ) by RLVECT_1:33;
then A6: ( b * ( v - w ) ) = ( ( b * ( v - u ) ) - ( a * ( v - u ) ) ) by A2,RLVECT_1:34
.= ( ( b - a ) * ( v - u ) ) by RLVECT_1:35
.= ( ( a - b ) * ( u - v ) ) by CKB5:1;
A7:now
assume a <> b;
then (( 0 ) < ( a - b ) or ( 0 ) < ( b - a )) by XREAL_1:55;
then (v,u // w,v or w,u // v,w) by A3,A4,A6,A5,CKB1:def 1;
hence thesis by CKB13:1;
end;
now
assume a = b;
then ( ( - u ) + v ) = ( ( - u ) + w ) by A2,A3,RLVECT_1:36;
then v = w by RLVECT_1:8;
hence thesis by CKB1:def 1;
end;
hence thesis by A7;
end;
hence thesis by CKB1:def 1;
end;
